        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:16.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "When he had spoken, the brahmin said to the Buddha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:16.2",
          "pli": "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama. ",
          "en": "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:16.3",
          "pli": "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evameva bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. ",
          "en": "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:16.4",
          "pli": "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. ",
          "en": "I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:16.5",
          "pli": "Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. ",
          "en": "Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:17.1",
          "pli": "Alattha kho bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ. ",
          "en": "And the brahmin received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:17.2",
          "pli": "Acirūpasampanno panāyasmā bhāradvājo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. ",
          "en": "Not long after his ordination, Venerable Bhāradvāja, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:17.3",
          "pli": "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. ",
          "en": "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:17.4",
          "pli": "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti. ",
          "en": "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:17.5",
          "pli": "Arahantavaggo paṭhamo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.1",
          "pli": "Dhanañjānī ca akkosaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.2",
          "pli": "asurindaṃ bilaṅgikaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.3",
          "pli": "Ahiṃsakaṃ jaṭā ceva, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.4",
          "pli": "suddhikañceva aggikā; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.5",
          "pli": "Sundarikaṃ bahudhīta—",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn7.10:18.6",
          "pli": "rena ca te dasāti. ",
          "en": ""
        }
